Replaces: systemd-zram-generator
Description: adaptive, calibrated zram-only swap manager
 Replaces systemd-zram-generator with a self-calibrating zram swap that scales in
 real time. A light bash daemon watches memory pressure (PSI) and hot-adds/removes
 whole zram devices (a live device cannot be resized) to grow and shrink swap
 without losing data — a device is only removed once its pages can migrate back.
 .
 The physical RAM a device may use is a percentage of the machine's real RAM
 (never a generic absolute value), enforced by the kernel's per-device mem_limit,
 so total zram use can never exceed the cap — worst case a write fails and the
 normal OOM path runs, never worse than a host with no zram. A Python calibrator
 measures this host's compression ratio and CPU cost to size the devices, and the
 daemon recalibrates when the live ratio drifts (e.g. a heatwave throttling the
 cores and slowing compression).
